<dl id="n10037c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10037c">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10037c"> 37(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> shortcut / path / bridgetoll</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Parmi les droits de la Couronne, le droit de <i>tonlieu</i> et de <i>p&eacute;age</i> n&apos;&eacute;tait point le moins fructueux. Partout o&ugrave; il y avait un pont, marchands et marchandises, b&ecirc;tes et gens devaient passer par ce pont, et il fallait acquitter le p&eacute;age. Au besoin, des cordes barraient la route voisine, qui aurait &eacute;t&eacute; plus facile, les plaines, les marais et jusqu&apos;aux bois. <font color="green">[Among the rights of the Crown, the right of tolls was not the least profitable. Wherever there was a bridge, merchants and merchandise, men and animals had to pay the toll in order to cross the bridge. Where necessary, ropes blocked off neighbouring routes that would have been easier&mdash;plains, marshes and even woods.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 46-7</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: French <i>Tonlieu</i>, a toll exercised at bridges and on ferries  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c01015e" href="c01all.htm#c01015e">VI.C.01:015(e)</a>, <a name="c01015f" href="c01all.htm#c01015f">VI.C.01:015(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
